    "body": "Yikes, you're right we should be consistent on this. Thanks!\r\n\r\n(Thinking out loud here.) At some point I used to prefer `amount` for tokens and `value` for ether (as in `msg.value`), but now that I think about it, \"token amount\" has always been very ambiguous because people expect it to not include the decimal digits, yet the smart contract needs all of the decimal digits. Maybe `value` is less ambiguous, precisely because it carries over the intuition from `msg.value` being expressed in wei.",
